                <div class="collapse" id="details-5">
                    <div class="row">
                        
    
        <div class="productInfo col-12">
        <P>This volume offers the author’s central articles on the medieval and early modern history of cartography for the first time in English translation. A first group of essays gives an overview of medieval cartography and illustrates the methods of cartographers. Another analyzes world maps and travel accounts in relation to mapped spaces. A third examines land surveying, cartographical practices of exploration, and the production of Portolan atlases. </P>
        </div>
    

